DataElement.preferredName: Person Clinical Trial Identifier Participation Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the unique identifier of a research study, a study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes, in which a person is participating or planning to participate.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the unique identifier of a research study, a study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes, in which a person is participating or planning to participate.

Property.preferredDefinition: A research study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes. Interventions include but are not restricted to drugs, cells and other biological products, surgical procedures, radiologic procedures, devices, behavioral treatments, process-of-care changes, and preventive care.:One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.:Taking part in an activity.

Concepts.definition: A research study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes.
One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.
The act of taking part in an activity.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: A type of research study that tests how well new medical treatments or other interventions work in people.  Such studies test new methods of screening, prevention, diagnosis, or treatment of a disease.  The study may be carried out in a clinic or other medical facility.  Also called a clinical trial.:Number; a concept of quantity derived from zero and units; a numeral or string of numerals that is used for identification.

Concepts.definition: Research conducted with human subjects or on material of human origin in which an investigator directly interacts with human subjects; includes development of new technologies, study of mechanisms of human diseases, therapy, clinical trials, epidemiologic, behavior, and health services research.
A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification.
